HEADWORD: Wreckage
<hw>Wreck"age</hw> <pr>(?; 48)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of wrecking, or state of being wrecked.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which has been wrecked; remains of a
wreck.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wrecker</ent>⟦br⟧
